a\not=1\in\mathbb R.
\left(a,\frac{a}{a-1}\right)
a+\frac{a}{a-1}=\frac{a^2}{a-1}=a\cdot\frac{a}{a-1}.
a\ge 2
a=2
a\ge2, a/(a-1)\ge2
\frac{a}{a-1}\ge 2\Rightarrow a\ge 2a-2\Rightarrow a\le 2\Rightarrow a=2.
(2,2)
2\frac{1}{3}+1\frac{3}{4}=2\frac{1}{3}\times1\frac{3}{4}
\frac{4}{5}+(-4)=\frac{4}{5}\times(-4)
1+2+3=1\cdot2\cdot3
